        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 7:05AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 704 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Tradinghouse Creek Reservoir to 6 miles
west of Crawford. Movement was south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Waco, Bellmead, Woodway, Lacy-Lakeview, McGregor, Beverly Hills,
Crawford, Hallsburg, Tradinghouse Creek Reservoir, and Lake Waco
around 710 AM CDT.
Hewitt and Robinson around 715 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Rock Creek,
Downsville, Willow Grove, Elm Mott, Tours, Ross, Asa, Spring Valley,
China Spring, and Leroy.

This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 314 and 348.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
